 supposed to be doing and bleh bleh bleh bleh bleh...<br><br>Who cares really...<br><br>Anyway I want to start a discussion about the POSSIBILITY of turning Zordak Ragefire into a Moderated Rotation. Much like they presently do with Nagfen and Vox. Now I'm sure there are about a ton of pro's and con's out there for such a rotation and if it were ever to come to this there would have to be rules to it.<br><br>So what I plan to do is to set up what this 'Moderated Rotation' would look like and give a list of rules and then hopefully get your thoughts and comments on it as well.<br><br>Please when you post to this thread state first if you would be For or Against such an idea and then feel free to give any comments or explanation's afterwards.<br><br>Also understand that I'm not attached to either way of doing things. I see merit to both a Moderated approach and to the present Camping approach. On the moderated side it would mean less fighting and squabbling and on the camping it lends more 'value' to the epic itself. This is only a thought that I think needs to be explored and if it doesn't work/fit then we toss it out. If it does work/fit then we worry about how it would be implimented.<br><br>So here we go.<br><br><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><center> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> *~*~*~*~*Zordak Ragefire - Moderated Rotation*~*~*~*~*</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></center><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Statement of Purpose:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>At present the Zordak Ragefire spawn is not only continually camped but is at present, a rare spawn that people are being forced to sit at for days if they wish to 'maintain their position' in the pecking order for Zordak.<br><br>     The purpose of the Moderated Rotation is to allow people to not only know when they are up for Zordak thus taking the guesswork out of 'who's next' but it's also to allow people with other commitments and Real Life things to attend to, to be able to fully enjoy not only the game, but one of the cooler aspects of being a high level cleric. (I.E. The Water Sprinkler of Nem Ankh or Rez Stick)<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Statement of Rules:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>At present the rules are fairly simple and are the following.<br>1.) The player requesting to be on the rotation must have a Cleric of at least 49th level or better.<br>2.) The player's character must have completed all previous steps and be in posession of the Shimmering Pearl used in the final step of the Epic Quest. (At present I'm unsure how to prove that you have the Shimmering Pearl as I'm not that far in the epic myself and have no idea if it's No-Drop or not, tho I'm betting it is. It could be something as simple as opening your inventory. Right clicking on the pearl and holding it then taking a screenshot like that then sending the SS to the Moderator via email. This will have to be figured out before it's put into effect.)<br><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><center> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> *~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></center><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br><br>Well that's all I've got thus far. Feel free to add, subtract and otherwise mangle this thing but please give your thoughts. ;-)<br><br>Seliah Moonwhisper &lt;Unification of Norrath&gt;<br>52nd Vicar of Bristlebane<br><br>&quot;SoW? Oh sure. Just a sec.&quot;<br>player_00 feels the favor of the gods upon them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufeydakinrainsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feydakin Rainsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/10/01 12:15:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=150.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zordak Ragefire on Rotation? (A Pro/Con Discussion)</span><hr size=1> Being the most desired and most &quot;valuable&quot; epic, and considering the stupidity of the current quest, there is no good way to start, maintain, or moderate a list for Ragefire.  The main problem is that this is a one-shot deal.  You can't have a &quot;rotation&quot; for a list that doesn't rotate, so forming a list reverts to arguments over how to start it &quot;fairly.&quot;  Unguilded or small-guild clerics may be proponents of a lottery-based list because it ensures they get their chance at some point (possibly very soon), and the list would mean they don't have to camp for the insane 150+ hour periods we see now.  However, larger guilds are just in saying that they are willing and able to hold the camp for those long times, and that entitles them to special consideration, and they won't accept a list based on random distribution of spots on that list.<br><br>It comes down to this:  If you want your epic badly enough, you will sit as long as you can stay awake, or you will arrange with friends/guildies to take shifts, and you will wait there until it's your turn, and if you make it long enough, and have enough friends to come help kill Ragefire, you'll have your rez-stick.  If not, that's why they call it &quot;epic.&quot;  It's supposed to be an item that's obtained with an extraordinary effort.  You and I both agree that the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> form</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that effort takes (camping for 150+ hours in a line that's sometimes 3, 4 or 5 people deep) is silly, but is beyond our power to change.<br><br>A list appeals to people that can't afford to undertake that camp.  However, there are still plenty of people who ARE willing to undertake the camp, and the system is working as it is.  If you doubt it, ask Ismena.<br><br> <p><CENTER>Feydakin Rainsong<BR>Wanderer of 52 Seasons<BR>Guild Officer<A HREF="http://droz.net/eq/azuresky">Azure Sky</A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upetoffen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Petoffen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/10/01 6:35:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=150.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/craig234/eq/petportrait.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zordak Ragefire on Rotation? (A Pro/Con Discussion)</span><hr size=1> Yes Fey, though I think there's a gray area on respecting when the cleric doesn't hold the camp, but has a feigned monk or whoever calling it for them - I get the impression many are not seeing that as a legit claim.<br><br>Luckily though the clerics themselves camping it (obviously with someone else at the keyboard at times over a 10 day 24 hour camp) is being respected. <p>Arch Mage 60, Master of the epic elemental magics, collector of robes<BR><a href="http://members.home.net/craig234/"target="web"><img src="http://members.home.net/craig234/eq/sig/petquotecrakerrcaniseepetattack.gif" border="0"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upetoffen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Petoffen</A> at: 8/10/01 6:36:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uyerrath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yerrath</A></span><br> <spa