ly increase the number of spawns by increasing prepairedness. (I.E. If you know it's your turn to do Zordak you'd more likely than not have the squad set to go on an hour or two's notice.) So my suggestion if this thing were to go active would be.<br><br>3.) The Cleric presently at the TOP of the list should be present in Sol B for the duration of their camp time until either<br>  A.) Zordak has spawned and they have killed him or<br>  B.) They have been bumped to the bottom of the list for whatever reason.<br><br>4.) If Zordak spawns the Cleric at the TOP of the list has 4 hours in which to gather their squad, buff and take Zordak down. This includes chatroom time. (I.E. Camping to Chat to save buffs and disucss strategy.) If 4 hours go by and the cleric is still unsuccessful in gathering the necessary people / resources / whatever then that cleric will be moved to the bottom of the list and the next cleric in line, and each cleric until zordak has been slain, will be granted 2 hours to prep a squad and kill him. Each person unsuccessful in gathering the necessary people in the allotted period of time will be bumped to the bottom of the list until someone is successful. (The reasoning for giving the initial cleric 4 hours and every one thereafter only 2 is during the 4 hour period of the first cleric the second cleric should have little problem quitely alerting people to be ready should the first clerics attempt fail. Thus the readyness factor is alot higher for each successive person after the first. The first of course SHOULD have people alert but in an unknown spawn time it can become very difficult to have people ready 24 / 7. Hence the extra 2 hours for the initial person.)<br><br>Thanks for everyone's comments thus far. Let's keep this going. ;-)<br><br>Seliah Moonwhisper &lt;Unification of Norrath&gt;<br>52nd Vicar of Bristlebane<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HRE